<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="595" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[812,1457,1537,1667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">DIAGNOSIS. — Wing with a small dark spot at the tip; Sc ends free. Thorax brown with pronotum and dorsal part of katepisternum yellow; fore coxa yellow, mid and hind coxa brown; metepimeron longer than hind coxa. Abdominal tergites and sternites 1-6 with a pale-yellow apical band; gonostyli slightly expanded at the tip.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="595" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[813,1455,1690,1741]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">ETYMOLOGY. — The name of this species refers to its infuscate wing apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="596" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[813,1455,1778,1900]" box="[813,957,1778,1804]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[813,1455,1778,1900]" box="[813,866,1810,1836]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis box="[813,866,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[813,1455,1778,1900]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1029,1841,1867]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">General coloration.</emphasis>
Dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1273,1841,1868]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,891,909]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,214,840]" captionTargetId="figure-421@4.[132,1455,203,863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — Habitus of new species of Lygistorrhina (Probolaeus) Williston,1896:A, Lygistorrhina maculipennis n. sp., with detached head in separate box; paratype MHNH-ED-ED10673; B, Lygistorrhina conica n. sp., paratype NMS-10003795; C, Lygistorrhina mitarakensis n. sp., paratype NMS-10003799. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321224" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321224/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); measurements, see 
<tableCitation box="[850,929,1873,1900]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="7.[337,348,218,236]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 1. — Measurements (length, in millimetres) for new species of Lygistorrhina (Probolaeus) Williston, 1896." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF15667E743B541BFEA7FF40FB09FF79" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" tableUuid="DF15667E743B541BFEA7FF40FB09FF79">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1455,1937,2028]" lastBlockId="5.[130,777,1236,1549]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="596" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,880,1937,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Head.</emphasis>
Rounded, dichoptic. Vertex slightly convex. Rounded ommatidia with subequal diameter, interocular setae subequal to ommatidial diameter. Three ocelli arranged almost in a straight line, with median ocellus slightly anteriad of two lateral ocelli. Antenna light brown, flagellomeres 1-6 yellow (
<figureCitation box="[141,217,1299,1326]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,891,909]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,214,840]" captionTargetId="figure-421@4.[132,1455,203,863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — Habitus of new species of Lygistorrhina (Probolaeus) Williston,1896:A, Lygistorrhina maculipennis n. sp., with detached head in separate box; paratype MHNH-ED-ED10673; B, Lygistorrhina conica n. sp., paratype NMS-10003795; C, Lygistorrhina mitarakensis n. sp., paratype NMS-10003799. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321224" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321224/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="596">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); antenna shorter than hind femur, length: 
<quantity box="[646,772,1300,1326]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.9">0.9-1.1 mm</quantity>
; 14 flagellomeres, with strong dorsal setae (flagellomeres 1-6: one pair, flagellomeres 7-14: two pairs), subcylindrical, gradually tapering; length of flagellomeres 1-6 1.3-1.6× their width, and 2-4× in flagellomeres 7-14. Face longer than wide. Clypeus with straight ventral edge. Palpus length 
<quantity box="[583,674,1459,1485]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
, tapering towards apex, with a simple row of long setae. Hypopharynx length 
<quantity box="[206,295,1522,1549]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="596" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
; labellum slightly longer.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4321226" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4321226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4321226/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="596" startId="5.[132,143,1070,1088]" targetBox="[132,775,215,1005]" targetPageId="5">
